sychology that constructs inwardness by telling all, blushing shame that delights in exposure, or dignity that refuses its lofty position? Failing Desire suggests that the power of these desires and pleasures comes out of the very realization that this question can never quite be answered.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aFailure (Psychology) 0aFailure (Psychology). 0aHumiliation. 0aShame. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Queer Studies. 4aLiterature : Comparative Literature. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Theology. 7aRELIGION / Sexuality & Gender Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2017z978311149102840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143846892140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438468921423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438468921/original  a978-3-11-149102-8  SUNY Press eBook Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles